OL,3,CMan fled country after conning drivers
OL,4,Cout of thousands of pounds
OL,6,FRiches carried out his crimes between
OL,7,F2009 and 2011, after he was an
OL,8,Femployee at Enterprise Rent-A-Car.
OL,9,FRiches left the car rental company to
OL,10,Fset up his own personal injury firm
OL,11,Fbut would contact his former
OL,12,Fcolleagues in order to illegally
OL,13,Fobtain the details of drivers, then
OL,14,Fcontacting them to offer his legal
OL,15,Fservices.
OL,17,FAt one point, through his accomplices
OL,18,FRiches had access to the internal
OL,19,FEnterprise database allowing him to
OL,20,Faccess the personal information of
OL,21,Fclients.
